      • readUserLoggedInInfo

        public void readUserLoggedInInfo(java.lang.String jsonResponse)
        Reads user's data from the app-server's response and initializes UserInfo with it. This function should be called after validating that the user has correctly logged in (i.e. after calling userLoggedInIsOk).
        Parameters:
        jsonResponse - The app-server's response to the login request

      • writeUserSignUpInfo

        public java.lang.String writeUserSignUpInfo(boolean isEditProfile)
        Writes user's data from UserInfo into a String JSON-formatted. Beware there are two different JSON formats due to the ugly-specified REST API on the shared-server side, so the boolean parameter is used to alternate between them.
        Parameters:
        isEditProfile - Should be true if the "edit profile" format is required
